                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>(Private)</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Cleveland</placeName>\n                <date>9<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> August 5618</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>Rev &amp; Dear Friend</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">I read every num-<lb/>ber of your valuable periodical with<lb/>\n                pleasurable interest, your leaders<lb/> especially possess for me great<lb/>\n                interest, I read and digest them<lb/> carefully and form <sic>judgement</sic>\n                in<lb/> accordance as they impress or con-<lb/>vince my intellect.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The popular style in<lb/> which these articles are written is\n                well<lb/> calculated to awaken thought and<lb/> their freedom from obstruse and<lb/>\n                pedantic argument makes them ac<lb/>ceptable to the practical men who<lb/> compose\n                the majority of your readers<lb/> and who have little time to devote<lb/> to the\n                study of learned disquisitions.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">There is one theme I am most<lb/> desirous you should at your\n                earliest<lb/> leisure prepare an article upon<lb/> either for a leader or not as\n                you<lb/> may please. It is respecting the faith<lb/> of the Israelite in the coming\n                of a<lb/> personal messiah. I would</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3bv7bg0s/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
