                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>suggest <del>your discuss</del> the title for the<lb/> article “Belief in the coming\n                of a personal<lb/> messiah” I would open the article<lb/> in something like the\n                following language<lb/> “One of the cardinal principles of faith<lb/> of a true\n                Israelite is a belief in a person-<lb/>-al messiah. It is one of the thirteen\n                    <del>a</del> fundamental articles<lb/> of our creed. It has been taught our<lb/>\n                Jewish youth <del>since</del> in the past it has<lb/> been the accepted belief of\n                all the great<lb/> Rabbis and learned teachers of <placeName>Israel</placeName><lb/>\n                <del>which</del> with a very few exceptions—and it is<lb/> so imbued into our\n                Religion as to make<lb/> it one of its most vital parts the removal<lb/> or\n                destruction of which would lead<lb/> to the dissolution of our Religion itself.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><del>Taught</del> Given in the Pentateuch taught<lb/> by the\n                Prophets inculcated by the Rabbins<lb/> and received by the Jewish youth from<lb/>\n                the beginning it has been and is still<lb/> one of the fundamental principles of\n                our<lb/> faith and must continue to be so long<lb/> as Judaism is preserved in its\n                pristine<lb/> purity and truth “&amp;c &amp;c or in similar<lb/> language—the\n                construction of the above<lb/> being imperfect from the haste in<lb/> which I have\n                written. After an ex-</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3bv7bg0s/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
